timestamp (1.5-1) unstable; urgency=low

  * Change optional argument [FORMAT] to optional option [-f/--format
    FORMAT], and add optional argument [LOGFILE]. This change is
    incompatible with version 1.4 of timestamp.
  * Reopen LOGFILE when SIGHUP is received, if LOGFILE was given (making
    it possible to do a killall -HUP timestamp after rotating logfiles
    written to via timestamp LOGFILE).

 -- Adam Sjøgren <asjo@koldfront.dk>  Tue, 23 Aug 2011 22:57:05 +0200

